<paragraph blockId="134.[151,1436,1543,2037]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName box="[151,319,1543,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Streblognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,319,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Streblognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small genus (two described species) restricted to southern Africa. It is notable for the large size of its workers and for its reproduction by gamergates.
</paragraph>
